{"/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_lavender_ver01/data/sn88078775/00340580758/1921031801/0511.xml":{"full_text":"ST\nv-\n4\nPAGE six\np,\nI\n1\nLU\n54 West Main\nSPRINGTIME--BUILD1NCTIME\nIf it be Repair Work,\nGarage or New Build\ning, call on us for our\nFREE PLAN SERVICE\nTHB\nR.B.WHITELUMBERCO\nPHONE 1981 OR 1088\nBUILDERS HARDWARE\nSASH AND DOORS\nLowe Bros. High Standard Paints\nPoultry Fencing and Netting\nGarden Tools and Plows\nScreen Doors and Windows\nLawn Mowers and Hose\nFishing Tackle of all Kind\nCALL 1611\nThe Crane-Krieg\nHardware Co\n11 S. Park Place\nA. Bailey\nThe Furnace Man\nBefore You Contract for the\nHeating\nof that New House\nliapjpjfam\nBuild Your Own Home\nAsk for one of our free plan\nbooks and let us help you to\na home of your own.\nWebb Webb\nLumber and\nBuilding Supplies\nPhone 1526 Yards, 6th Wilson\nPhone 1342\nALL OF US want to see good times\nreturn when the worker will be em\nployed at fair wages, the merchant\ndoing business at a reasonable profit,\nand the factories running at maxi\nmum capacity.\nAn all of us\u2014everyone of us\u2014can\nhelp bring about this condition.\nThe first thing to do is to squarely\nface the facts and, above all, let\u2019s try\nnot to deceive ourselves.\nI All the financial, economic 0*\n[political preventives in the world\ncould not have checked the present\ndepression. The people made up\ntheir minds it was coming\u2014and it\ncame. As soon as the people make\nup their minds it has run its course\nit will end. In other words, depres\nsions are psychological mass fear\nbrings them on mass confidence ends\nthem.\nLaying aside all the incidental de\ntails, the big thing to do is to bring\nabout mass confidence, and there cer\ntainly is plenty of material at hand\nwith which to do this.\nMore than 2,000,000 homes are\nneeded\u2014and badly needed\u2014RIGHT\nNOW. This does not include factories\nand business houses. These buildings\nsimply MUST be erected sooner or\nlater, and an additional demand is\naccumulating while their erection is\nbeing delayed. This means that the\ncost of building probably will be much\nhigher in the future than it is now.\nJust as soon as a few far-sighted\nmen in each community shake off the\nfear that grips them and begin to\nbuild, others will become more confi\ndent and trail along. Thus will pros\nperity be restored to the building in\ndustry, and it will be a good many\nyears before there will be a let-up\nIn other lines of endeavor, from\ndigging ditches to running railroads,\nthe return of prosperity depends upon\nthe every-day buyer of ordinary\nmerchandise. In order to illustrate,\nsuppose we put it this way:\nIn every community there are sev\neral hundred men who need new\nsuits, but are delaying buying because\nthey are afraid of the future and\nwant to keep every cent they have\nthey also hope that prices will go\nlower.\nWhen these several hundred men\nin each community are combined, it\nmeans several million for the entire\ncountry.\nThere is very little likelihood of the\nprice of clothing going to a lower\nlevel. Present indications are that\nit will go higher. Supose these mil\nlions of men who actually need suits\nbuy Uiis week. It would mean in\ncreased business in the stores, with\nmore clerks employed. Ift. would\nman a revival in 1he textile industries\nINSURANCE\nLife\nFire\nTornado\nAutomobile\nLiability, &c.\nThe HAYDEN\nINSURANCE AGENCY CO.\nFifth and Church Sts,\nNEWARK\n13 South 4th St\nTT E NEWARK LEADER\nProsperity\nwith thousands of new operatives.\nIt would mean the purchase of new\nmachinery by the manufacturers,\nwho would have to call upon the\nsteei mills for their product, and the\nlatter would send in a hurry call to\nthe ore mines. And all these dif\nferent orders would be reflected in\nadditions to the crews on the rail\nroads which would be called upon to\ntransport the various items.\nSo it can easily be seen that the\nreturn of prosperity is \u201cup to\u201d the\nevery-day citizen who is holding\nback from buying needed articles\ncause he is afraid of the future,\nthe men with available cash will\ngin to build, and the men who\nworking will buy what they need,\nprosperity simply can\u2019t be kept away.\nbe\nIf\nbe\nare\nLet\u2019s get this fear out of our hearts\n\u2014jump in and set the wheels of in\ndustry to humming again. A great\ntruth came out of Wall street one\ntime when a speculator said no man\ncould be a \u201cbear\" on America and\nkeep from going broke. Prosperity\nhas to come\u2014it can\u2019t be kept away.\nSo why not bow to the inevitable and\nhelp it along?\nApproximately 17,000 workers are\nidle in the eight counties served by\nthe state employment bureau in AP\ntoona, Pa. Of this number 2,000 are\nmen who came into the district look\ning for work. Industries that have\nclosed, and those that are run\nning with materially reduced forces or\nare on part time, Include railroad, silk,\ncoal, iron, candy, paper, woolen, stone,\nbrick and lumber operations. Ordinar\nily 70,000 men are employed in indus\ntrial pursuits In Blair, Cambria, Clear\nfield, Jefferson, Center, Bedford, Hunt\ningdon and Fulton counties.\nTwo big motortruck plants, the foun\ndries and several of the smaller con\ncerns at Lima, O., are planning to re\nsume operations on a full-time basis\nwithin the next two months.\nThe executive council of the Belgian\nFederation of Labor has approved a\nlaw prohibiting virtually ail buisness\nactivity between six o\u2019clock Sunday\nmorning and the same hour Monday\nmorning. This measure also forbids\nthe sale of newspapers and periodicals\nbetween three o\u2019clock Sunday after\nnoon and the same hour Monday, ex\ncept on the occasion of elections.\nTwo big cotton mills near Columbus,\nGa., the Eagle and Phenix, and the\nSwift Manufacturing company plants\nannounced resumption of full-time op\neration after two months of half time.\nNo wage reductions will be made, it\nwas stated, but bonus payments are\ndiscontinued.\nThe St. Louis and San Francisco\nrailroad announced a reduction In the\npay of maintenance of way employees,\nat Houston, Texas, from 42 cents an\nhour to 25 cents. Local officers of\nthe railroad brotherhood declare the\ncut was in violation of the national\nagreement\nAn error whereby the word \u201cpaint\ners\u201d was rendered \u201cprinters\u201d was re\nsponsible for press dispatches that\nGadsden (Ala.) union printers had\nvoluntarily reduced their wage scale\nfrom 75 cents to 65 cents. The paint\ners announced the reduction and the\nprinters wore In no way involved.\nA\nJ.W.WEAKLEY\nTin and Slate\nRoofing\nSheet Iron Copper\nWork\nand Spouting\nAgent For\nRAVENNA and FARQUAR\nFURNACES\n141 Indiana St., Newark, O\nDEAN BROS\nAuto Phone 1725\nALL KINDS OF\nPlumbing and Pump Work\nHand and Power Pumps\nAssociated Gas Engines\n.......t\n[2\nPhone 2702\n^M^v**\u2122**^^\nFRIDAY, MARCH ISlh, 1921\nPeople of Small Means\nAre as welcome to participate in the benefits\nconferred by this Bank\nas are men of wealth\nPeople who desire to open a modest checking account,\ninvest money or embark in a business enter\nprise are invited to confer with the\nofficers of this bank\nThe Licking Co. Bank\nand Trust Co\nNEWARK, OHIO\nIF YOU NEED A HOUSE LIKE THIS,\nNOW IS THE TIME TO BUILD.\nLumber is now down 50^ below last year\u2019s\nprice and at Bed Rock\nTHE P. SMITH SENS LUMBER CO\nTHE MARIETTA\nPAINT AND COLOR CO\nPaints, Oils, Varnishes,\nStains, Fillers\nCoaters, Brushes, Etc\n28 Arcade and 31W. Church St\nGeo. T. Stream\nPlumbing and Heating\n\u201cDAYTON BICYCLES\u201d\nGUARANTEED FOR 5 YEARS\nPhone 1370 78 W. Main St\nBUILD THAT NEW HOUSE\nNOW!","height":"26661","width":"18357"}}
